modules.description: This module provides functions to pretty-print the internal structure of documents before and after rendering. It works with `SmartPrint.t` values, which represent structured documents. Use `pp_document` to visualize the layout of a document, and `pp_document_after_rendering` to inspect its structure after spaces have been transformed into newlines at specified indentation levels.

This module provides functions to pretty-print primitive OCaml values like unit, bool, int, float, and string, as well as structured types like option, list, and tuple. It generates output in a human-readable format suitable for debugging or logging specific values. Use cases include inspecting complex nested data structures during development or formatting expressions for code generation.

This module structures and renders documents with precise layout control through concatenation, grouping, and indentation, operating on a `t` type that supports transformations like delimiter wrapping and separator insertion. Its submodules enable inspection of document layouts before and after rendering, using functions like `pp_document` and `pp_document_after_rendering`, while also providing utilities to pretty-print primitive and structured OCaml values for debugging or code generation. You can generate readable code, visualize document structure, or format nested data such as lists and tuples with customizable indentation and line breaks.
